title: Assistant Clinic Manager
description_1: Began as a registered behavior therapist, providing 1:1 ABA therapy to children with autism spectrum disorder. Promoted to ABA trainer where I trained new employees on ABA fundamentals and prepared for RBT certification. Then promoted to Assistant Clinic Manager, where I took on all administrative roles crucial to the day-to-day functioning of the center. This included scheduling staff and clients, hiring and onboarding processes, managing over 65 staff members, facilitating family communication, and being the point of contact individual for all outside personnel. This role allowed me to develop exceptional leadership and management skills, customer service experience, and scheduling and billing procedures.

title: Student Recruitment Assistant
description_1: Worked under the director of student recruitment and outreach for The College of Liberal Arts and Sciences aiding potential first year students through the application and college decision process. Regularly communicated with students and families via phone and email, and spoke at university events. This role taught me professional practices, the behind the scenes of higher education, and valuable administrative skills.

title: Honors Thesis
description_1: Conducted independent research study under the supervision and mentorship of committee members. Had a role in all steps of the research process including formulating research questions, study creation, database management, participant recruitment, data collection, statistical analyses, creating a research paper and poster for presentation. Gained knowledge on IRB process, protocol formulation, creating and utilizing software programs for data analysis.

title: Post-Bacc Researcher
description_1: Research assistant in a study of the role of executive function on health-related quality of life in children and adolescents with congenital heart disease. Involved with participant screening and recruitment, obtaining informed consent, working on protocol development, administering cognitive assessments and surveys, data entry and analyses. Trained in HIPAA regulations, IRB regulations, and compliance. I had to leave prematurely when study was paused due to COVID.

title: Research Assistant
description_1: Served as an undergraduate research assistant in multiple psychology, cognitive, and biological labs. Trained in EEG studies, participant recruitment, informed consent, protocol development, data collection, data entry and analysis, and additional administrative tasks in the lab.
